ideas.} 13. Bc2 Nb8 {The knight is headed to d7. Black's c-pawn is now free to 
move.} 14. b4 Nbd7 15. Bb2 {White is building up his position quite slowly.} g6 
{Black plays slowly as well, fianchettoing his bishop. The immediate c5 is also 
interesting.} 16. Qb1 {White also looks to improve the position of his queen.} 
Bg7 {Rb8 is also good.} 17. Nb3 {The knight is headed for a5.} Rc8 18. Na5 {Now 
Black's bishop is attacked.} Ba8 19. d5 {White has a daunting space advantage.} 
*

