O-O 9. h3 Nb8 {Nb8 is known as the Breyer Variation. It is one of the most solid 
ways to play for Black against the Ruy Lopez and has maintained a fantastic 
reputation for many years.} 10. d4 {White grabs the center.} Nbd7 {This is the 
idea behind the Nb8 move. Black reroutes his knight to a better square on d7, 
and the c-pawn becomes mobile.} 11. Nbd2 Bb7 {Black fianchettos his bishop.} 12. 
