1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 {Black begins by kicking away the bishop with 
3...a6} 4. Ba4 Nf6 {Black continues his development.} 5. O-O {White castles and 
allows Black to make a choice. Be7 heads towards a Closed Spanish Structure 
while Nxe4 would lead to a more open position.} Be7 {Black places the bishop on 
e7, threatening Nxe4.} 6. Re1 {White guards the pawn with his rook.} b5 {Black 
plays b5 to stop Bxc6 followed by Nxe5 ideas.} 7. Bb3 {The bishop retreats to 
b3.} O-O {Black maintains the flexibility of playing either d6, the Closed 
Spanish, or d5, the Marshall Attack.} 8. c3 {White prepares to play d4 and 
creates a square on c2 for his bishop in case Black tries to play Na5.} d5 
{Black goes for the Marshall Attack. Black sacrifices a pawn for initiative on 
the kingside.} 9. exd5 {White grabs the pawn. The e5-pawn will be hanging next. 
From here, lines are very forcing and White will retain and edge.} *

[Event "Ruy Lopez: Masterclass Edition"]
