to the kingside in search of safety.} 10. Nc3 {White continues his development.} 
Be7 {By playing Be7, Black prepares to trade knights.} 11. Rd1 Nh4 {White should 
allow the knight trade.} 12. Nxh4 Bxh4 13. Ne2 {The White knight is headed to a 
more active post.} Be7 14. Be3 {White completes his development.} h5 15. Rd2 
{White wants to double up.} h4 16. Rad1 Rh5 {An interesting way of hitting the 
e5-pawn.} 17. Bf4 {Now the theory ends. The fight will continue.} *

