on b5.} 7. Be2 {The bishop comes back to e2. Ba4 is also fine.} Nxe4 8. dxc5 {It 
is better to take the bishop rather than the knight because the bishop pair will 
give White an advantage in these kinds of open positions. White's only problem 
is that he has slightly weakened his pawn structure.} Nxc5 {Black greedily grabs 
the c5-pawn.} 9. Qd4 {A nice move, centralizing the queen and hitting both 
knights. Now Black has some problems to deal with and White will win back the 
pawn.} d6 10. f4 {Attacking the knight.} Ng6 11. Qxg7 {White wins back the 
pawn.} *

