1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 f5 {This is the exciting Schliemann Gambit. Black 
typically sacrifices a pawn for exciting, open positions. If White is 
knowledgable about this line however, he will achieve a good position.} 4. Nc3 
{Nc3 is the best move, protecting e4.} fxe4 {Black takes on e4.} 5. Nxe4 {White 
recaptures. From here, Black will play either 5...Nf6 or 5...d5, which lead to 
very sharp play. Lines after 5...d5 are especially sharp.} *

