1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 f5 4. Nc3 fxe4 5. Nxe4 d5 {Play becomes very sharp 
and it is important to play precisely.} 6. Nxe5 {White takes advantage of the 
pin.} dxe4 {Black takes on e4.} 7. Nxc6 {Now Black has to choose between the 
main line Qg5 and also rather popular move Qd5.} Qd5 {This is a popular sideline 
at the club level.} 8. c4 {Hitting the queen.} Qd6 9. Nxa7+ {White takes the 
pawn with check.} Bd7 10. Bxd7+ {White accepts the trade.} Qxd7 11. Qh5+ {Now 
the queen comes in with check.} g6 12. Qe5+ Kf7 {Black prepares to meet Qxh8 
with Bg7.} 13. Nb5 c6 14. Qd4 {After the queen trade, White stands better.} *

