the pawn.} 8. Bxc6 {White wins the e5-pawn.} dxc6 9. Nxe5 {White does not 
hesitate to grab the pawn.} Bf5 10. O-O O-O 11. d4 {White grabs some center 
control.} Bd6 12. f4 {White ensures that he will create a strong passed pawn if 
Black takes on e5.} Bxe5 {Black does choose to capture.} 13. dxe5 Qg6 14. Rf2 
{Defending c2. White is up a pawn and it is a passer.} *

