is staring at his own pawn.} c6 7. Ba4 {White does not want to allow d5 with 
tempo.} Ne7 8. f4 {White gains kingside space and has easy play.} *

[Event "Ruy Lopez: Masterclass Edition"]
[Site "Sidelines"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Classical Variation 1"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "10 Sidelines"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "ruy-lopez-masterclass-edition/course/3489, variation/114752"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 {Bc5 is known as the Classical Variation. Black 
develops his bishop naturally to the c5 square.} 4. c3 {Preparing d4. d4 will be 
played with tempo, which demonstrates that the bishop is misplaced on c5.} Nf6 
{Black continues to develop very classically.} 5. d4 {With tempo on the bishop.} 
Bb6 {The bishop drops back.} 6. O-O O-O 7. Bg5 {White threatens dxe5.} h6 
{Kicking away the bishop.} 8. Bh4 {The bishop drops back.} d6 {Black supports 
his pawn on e5 and frees a diagonal for his light-squared bishop.} 9. Qd3 {White 
has a bigger center and a much easier position to play.} *

[Event "Ruy Lopez: Masterclass Edition"]
[Site "Sidelines"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Classical Variation 2"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "10 Sidelines"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "ruy-lopez-masterclass-edition/course/3489, variation/114751"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 {Bc5 is known as the Classical Variation. Black 
develops his bishop naturally to the c5 square.} 4. c3 {Preparing d4. d4 will be 
played with tempo, which demonstrates that the bishop is misplaced on c5.} f5 
{This is a more aggressive try. However, White is doing well if he opens the 
position with d4.} 5. d4 {White rips open the position. Play becomes very 
forcing.} fxe4 {White takes the e-pawn, hitting the knight.} 6. Bxc6 {This is 
key. Now exf3 can be met by Bxf3, which is much better for White.} dxc6 7. Nxe5 
{White has the better pawn structure.} Bd6 8. Qh5+ {The king is also exposed.} 
g6 9. Qe2 {The queen drops back. Black has the bishop pair, but White's knight 
on e5 is a monster and White has the better pawn structure. Black's king is also 
weak.} *

