[Comment "ruy-lopez-masterclass-edition/course/3489, variation/114746"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 {Black kicks away the bishop.} 4. Ba4 f5 {Now 
Black lashes out with f5. This is called the Schliemann Gambit Deferred because 
Black has played a6 before going for f5.} 5. d4 {White tries to open up lines.} 
exd4 {This is the first capture possible in the position.} 6. e5 {White 
sacrifices the pawn for strong compensation.} Bc5 7. O-O {White brings his own 
king to safety.} Nge7 8. Bb3 {White prevents Black from castling.} d5 {Black 
tries to create an opportunity to castle.} 9. exd6 {White makes sure that Black 
is not able to castle.} Qxd6 10. Re1 Bd7 11. Nbd2 {White's minor pieces now 
become very annoying.} O-O-O 12. Nc4 {Despite being down a pawn, White is likely 
to win it back in the future. The engine evaluation of this position is +0.5 for 
White.} *

